SUMMARY:Remixed: Florida Artists Look at Art History
LOCATION:1501 N. Nebraska Avenue Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:oanna Robotham\, Curator of Modern and Contemporary Art at the
  Tampa Museum of Art\, will present a talk on Florida artists Pepe Mar\, M
 ernet Larsen\, Purvis Young\, and Theo Wujcik. Inspired by art history\, t
 he artists create unique artworks that demonstrate the influence of Old Ma
 ster painters\, the Russian Avant-Garde\, the Impressionists\, and 20th-ce
 ntury trailblazers. This presentation will highlight how contemporary arti
 sts have created a union between the past and the present in their works o
 f art. Pepe Mar\, Mernet Larsen\, Purvis Young\, and Theo Wujciks art are 
 part of the Tampa Museum of Arts permanent collection. They are featured a
 rtists in the poster exhibition Made in Florida\, on view across the Hills
 borough County Library system. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/1
 92206
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/192206
